{"type":"message","id":"45908adb","parentId":"6701c774","timestamp":"2026-02-17T12:15:05.762Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:10a19bb7-7afb-4b24-8478-62555b540c2d daily-ping-telegram] Send the daily ping to Telegram (ID: 1087368827). Fetch: 1) Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API (https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true), 2) Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance, 3) Top 5 GitHub repos by stars (https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5). Format as a concise morning summary with emoji and send via message tool to Telegram target 1087368827.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, February 17th, 2026 — 8:15 PM (Asia/Singapore)"}],"timestamp":1771330505759}}
{"type":"message","id":"68e8f60a","parentId":"45908adb","timestamp":"2026-02-17T12:15:20.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to send a daily ping message to Telegram with:\n1. Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API\n2. Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance\n3. Top 5 GitHub repos by stars\n\nLet me start by fetching the Bitcoin price and GitHub repos using web_fetch, and then I'll need to use yfinance for the stock prices.\n\nActually, for the stocks I should use yfinance which is a Python library. Let me use exec to run a Python script that gets the stock prices.\n\nLet me do these in parallel where possible:\n1. Fetch Bitcoin price via web_fetch\n2. Fetch GitHub repos via web_fetch\n3. Get","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Fetching Bitcoin price, stock data, and GitHub trending"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:0","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.exec:2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\n\ntickers = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\nfor symbol in tickers:\n    try:\n        stock = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n        hist = stock.history(period='2d')\n        if len(hist) >= 2:\n            current = hist['Close'].iloc[-1]\n            prev = hist['Close'].iloc[-2]\n            change = ((current - prev) / prev) * 100\n            results[symbol] = {\n                'price': round(current, 2),\n                'change': round(change, 2)\n            }\n        else:\n            info = stock.info\n            current = info.get('regularMarketPrice', 0)\n            prev_close = info.get('regularMarketPreviousClose', current)\n            change = ((current - prev_close) / prev_close) * 100 if prev_close else 0\n            results[symbol] = {\n                'price': round(current, 2),\n                'change': round(change, 2)\n            }\n    except Exception as e:\n        results[symbol] = {'price': 0, 'change': 0, 'error': str(e)}\n\nprint(json.dumps(results))\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":9415,"output":570,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9985,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771330505761}}
